The paper discusses the challenges and potential solutions for resource allocation in next-generation wireless networks, specifically 5G networks. This topic falls under the category of computer networks and the sub-category of network architecture and design (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of algorithms and optimization techniques, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the need for distributed implementation and dealing with users' selfishness, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and game theory (cs.GT).
